The  European Central Bank  said
financial institutions increased overnight deposits to the
highest in 15 months.  Euro-area banks placed 255.6 billion euros ($344.6 billion)
at the Frankfurt-based ECB on Oct. 7, up from 229 billion euros
the previous day. Thatâ€™s the highest since June 30, 2010.
Financial institutions borrowed 2.8 billion euros at  the
marginal rate of 2.25 percent, up from 1.8 billion euros the
